      '<p>The role would suit candidates with experience in consumer internet businesses or fast-growth startups that want to build a new market-leader from the ground up. The position would suit mid-level or senior technologists who are looking to move back into a hands-on role, relocate to Lisbon and are attracted by a salary + equity package. The company has built a working V1 of its product and is looking for a talented engineer to work alongside a founder with one successful exit to his name already in driving the product roadmap and hiring the first tech employees.</p>\n\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Hands-on with the code, building the business from the ground up</li>\n<li>Provide technology guidance for the company</li>\n<li>Build a team from scratch and develop the engineering talent</li>\n<li>Maintain a high bar for recruiting, hiring and performance of the engineering team</li>\n<li>Provide hands-on technical management, guidance, and support including system/design/code review</li>\n<li>You will be responsible for the health of your teams\' systems and technologies</li>\n<li>Promote overall engineering excellence and best practices</li>\n<li>Establish a strong innovation based engineering culture within the Technology team and the company as a whole</li>\n<li>Create a technology vision and roadmap based on opportunities &amp; risks for the company\u2019s business. Push boundaries of technical innovation within the company</li>\n</ul><p>Technologies/Work Areas:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>HTML5 </li>\n<li>CSS3 </li>\n<li>JavaScript</li>\n<li>Angular Docs </li>\n<li>TypeScript</li>\n<li>NodeJS</li>\n<li>MongoDB</li>\n<li>Amazon Web Services </li>\n<li>Jenkins</li>\n<li>SEO</li>\n<li>Google Analytics</li>\n</ul><p>Requirements:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor\u2019s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering or equivalent work experience</li>\n<li>Strong sense of ownership</li>\n<li>The ability to balance business needs, a sense of urgency, and shipping high quality and pragmatic solutions</li>\n<li>Experience in building and maturing engineering teams in a startup environment</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of common Web technologies</li>\n<li>Extensive experience with cross functional teams and managing relationships with business or operations stakeholders</li>\n<li>People management experience, preferably managing first-line managers</li>\n<li>Thinks strategically - develops process, tools and frameworks that help ensure effectiveness across a variety of stakeholders</li>\n<li>Pragmatic expert in software and architecture best practices</li>\n<li>Fluent English</li>\n</ul><p>Desirable:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Strong analytical skills</li>\n<li>Contributions to the technical communities (e.g. open source, blogging, etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience with machine learning and/or data modeling</li>\n<li>Experience of having worked in a classifieds or price comparison business</li>\n<li>Experience with b2b systems, working with enterprise customers</li>\n<li>Experience with advertising, especially in the consumer space</li>\n<li>Experience with large and complex product catalogs and/or other structured big data</li>\n<li>8+ years of Technology and Engineering experience, of which some in a management role</li>\n</ul>',
