      'Full Time',
      '<p><a href=\'https://Rehab.com\'>Rehab.com</a> is hiring a highly experienced, strategic <strong>CTO/Lead Developer</strong> to build and scale our technical team, and take it to new heights. The right person will have a strong technical background and a deep knowledge of product management, including being able to generate smart product roadmaps. </p>\n\n<p>We\u2019re putting together a totally new team. You will lead the exciting redevelopment of our site architecture, database design, (UX/UI) and general development. To execute, you\u2019ll build out our new technical team, including full knowledge transfer from the old team. </p>\n\n<p>We\'re looking for someone with a deep understanding of consumer internet products (primarily online booking agents -- OBAs), as well as experience defining system architecture and SEO architecture. </p>\n\n<p>Creating reliable, scalable, high-performance products requires exceptional technical expertise as well as strong leadership. We are seeking a skilled, well-rounded lead developer with both extensive backend experience and a strong grasp of front-end needs (UI/UX).</p>\n\n<p>Required:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>10+ years experience as a software developer</li>\n<li>Experience defining system architectures and exploring technical feasibility trade-offs, including SEO architectures and HTML best practices</li>\n<li>Thorough knowledge of consumer internet products, and the importance of a quality content/publisher strategy </li>\n<li>Experience with SEO and search engine development, especially using ElasticSearch</li>\n<li>Expertise in exploiting backlinks</li>\n<li>Willingness to work remotely, with monthly travel to Scottsdale, AZ (our current HQ)</li>\n<li>Previous startup experience, and comfort in a lean startup environment</li>\n<li>Deep expertise in at least one of the following: PHP, Ruby or Java</li>\n</ul><p>Preferred:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Knowledge of SCRUM or similar agile methodologies</li>\n<li>Knowledge of professional software engineering practices and best practices for the full software development life cycle, including coding standards, code reviews, source control management, build processes, testing, and operations</li>\n<li>Experience mentoring junior software engineers to improve their skills, making them more efficient and effective </li>\n<li>Experience communicating with users, other technical teams, and senior management to collect requirements, describe software product features, technical designs, and product strategy</li>\n<li>Understanding of backlink significance</li>\n<li>Experience in security: data management, PII, servers and anti-scrapping measures</li>\n</ul><p>Bonus Points:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>As we are a rehab site, someone in recovery is a plus</li>\n<li>Motivated by complicated challenges, aggressive timelines and pressure is a plus </li>\n</ul><p>Required Technical Skills:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>HP (advanced)</li>\n<li>SQL (advanced) </li>\n<li>Symfony 2 or 3 (advanced)</li>\n<li>Doctrine 2+ (advanced)</li>\n<li>ElasticSearch 3+</li>\n<li>HTML5</li>\n<li>Jquery</li>\n<li>Twitter Bootstrap 3+</li>\n<li>CSS</li>\n<li>Apache 2.4+</li>\n<li>Ruby on Rails</li>\n<li>ReactJS</li>\n<li>Redis</li>\n</ul><p>Preferred: </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>NodeJS</li>\n<li>Redux</li>\n<li>LESS</li>\n<li>Nginx</li>\n<li>REST</li>\n<li>Docker</li>\n<li>Unit Testing</li>\n<li>BASH scripting</li>\n<li>Mobile app development</li>\n</ul><p>We look forward to hearing from you. We may be reached at: <a href=\'mailto:cto-job@rehab.com\'>cto-job@rehab.com</a></p>',
      '<p>Email your resume to: <a href=\'mailto:cto-job@rehab.com\'>cto-job@rehab.com</a>.</p>',
