      'Full Time',
      '<h2>Open Publishing Is Looking For A Fullstack REACT Developer</h2>\n\n<p><em>Open Publishing is looking for a Javascript expert to bring our UI and UX to the next level.</em></p>\n\n<p>At Open Publishing we build the infrastructure for the publishing of the future. Open Publishing covers the whole value chain of publishing from e-book production to distribution, marketing, reporting and royalty management. In 2018, Open Publishing became the largest German e-book distribution platform, used by more than 100 publishing houses. The software also powers high-performance websites with 30 millions visits and seven figure turnover annually. Open Publishing was founded in 1998 and has about 40 employees.</p>\n\n<h2>About The Position / Your Responsibilities</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Take responsibility for the frontend of our publishing suite for cutting edge publishing services</li>\n<li>Develop the UI and UX of the websites and optimize conversions</li>\n<li>Cooperate closely with the backend developers to build a great product and great features</li>\n<li>Participate and prepare software design decisions and code reviews</li>\n<li>We are on the way to a micro service oriented architecture</li>\n<li>Be part of an agile Scrum team in Munich and the Ukraine</li>\n</ul><h2>About You</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>You have experience with Javascript, React and ideally some experience with C++ and/or Python</li>\n<li>Experience with testing frameworks and Cucumber is valuable</li>\n<li>3-5 years of professional software development experience</li>\n<li>Full-stack mindset</li>\n<li>Extensive experience with REST APIs</li>\n<li>Solid understanding of service-oriented infrastructure/architecture</li>\n<li>Good understanding of the challenges of a good user interface and the joys of conversion optimization</li>\n<li>Test- and behavior driven development is not foreign to you</li>\n<li>You value clean code</li>\n<li>You are not afraid to work with code from others</li>\n<li>Docker-experience is highly appreciated</li>\n<li>Academic degrees are great, but not required if you have the right experience</li>\n<li>You are fluent in English and ideally but not mandatory German</li>\n</ul><h2>What We Offer</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Agile environment\nHelp with relocation and work permit if necessary</li>\n<li>Great office in the heart of Munich</li>\n<li>Competitive salary</li>\n<li>Full health / dental insurance plan in Germany\u2019s high-class public health system</li>\n<li>28 vacation days plus 12 Bavarian holidays (no other German state has more)</li>\n<li>Paid work-related training (i.e. conferences, workshops, etc.)</li>\n<li>German language class for international applicants. </li>\n</ul><h2>How To Apply</h2>\n\n<p>Please email your CV and a cover letter explaining how your qualifications and experience meet the requirements of this job description. Email should be sent to <a href=\'mailto:jobs@openpublishing.com\'>jobs@openpublishing.com</a>.</p>',
