      'Full Time',
      '<p><strong>Tweddle Group</strong> is looking for Software Engineers interested in joining our Product Development team. Team members are building platforms for advanced vehicle diagnostics, digital owner information, and service portals. Tweddle Group is headquartered in Clinton Township, Michigan with international offices in Italy, Belgium, and Shanghai. Our Product Development team is located in downtown Detroit</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for <strong>Engineers with Python and React experience</strong> to drive the next iteration of our vehicle diagnostic platform. We are looking for a full-stack engineer because individual product teams are responsible for their entire product\'s infrastructure.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for <strong>Engineers with Java, Spring, and ElasticSearch experience</strong> to continue building and scaling our information delivery systems. We are looking for engineers with back-end experience, devops, and knowledge of the front-end because product teams are responsible for their entire product top to bottom.</p>\n\n<p>What you bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A getting stuff done attitude (GSD)</li>\n<li>Strong understanding of REST APIs and their implementation</li>\n<li>Experience building and hosting in one of the following:\n\n<ul>\n<li>Python/Python3 backend applications (Flask/Django experience is a bonus)</li>\n<li>Java/Spring backend applications (ElasticSearch experience is a bonus)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Experience building and deploying React applications (Redux experience is a bonus)</li>\n<li>Familiarity with deploying and maintaining scalable applications on AWS</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of GIT how to use GIT in a team setting</li>\n<li>Experience with agile/scrum development methodologies</li>\n</ul><p>What we bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work from home friendly </li>\n<li>Opportunity to work in Detroit WeWork locations</li>\n<li>Flexible working hours</li>\n<li>Project ownership opportunities</li>\n<li>Open-minded engineering culture</li>\n</ul>',
