      'Senior Java Developer - Tools Team',
      'London, UK',
      'Full Time',
      '<p>Interested in scalability? With over 200 million monthly active users from our popular games franchises including Candy Crush, Farm Heroes and Bubble Witch, being able to handle ridiculously-high volumes of data and traffic is the name of the game. Working within our Shared Technology Department, you\u2019ll get to work on business-critical systems that support these users. Whether it\u2019s core data engineering, user acquisition technology, vital tools that are needed by our games teams, or reporting and visualisation suites, there\u2019s an exciting opportunity for you here to get stuck into within Shared Technology - and one you can get stuck into right away!</p>\n\n<p>With games being the life-blood of our business, we\u2019re searching for a passionate, talented Senior Java Developer to join our dedicated Games Tools Team. The Tools suite enables our smash-hit games to perform vital, common functions so that they can continue to be a success.</p>\n\n<p>Your role within our Kingdom</p>\n\n<p>A Senior Java Developer can expect to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Develop features: design/architect, implement and maintain business/tools features</li>\n<li>Consider non-functional requirements: ensure the high performance, reliability, scalability and security of our systems</li>\n<li>Deliver code - and supporting documentation - of the highest quality through good design, attention to detail and system testing on a timely basis</li>\n<li>Share knowledge and help colleagues both inside and outside of your team</li>\n<li>Advocate and follow best practices<br>\n</li>\n</ul><p>Skills to create thrills</p>\n\n<p>You have a strong passion for building backend technologies in a Java-based environment. You\'re an excellent communicator, happy to work with people from several different business units. You can translate business needs into technical requirements and implementation. You\'re excited about doing what\'s best for the team, and adaptable enough to work on different things as projects evolve. You\u2019re keen to work in a fun and friendly environment.</p>\n\n<p>Other skills include:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Strong experience with Java, databases and caching (at least Java 8)<br>\n</li>\n<li>Commercial experience of Gradle and Docker/container environment<br>\n</li>\n<li>Testing frameworks and integration tests<br>\n</li>\n<li>Care for code quality, and robust, easily-maintainable architectural solutions<br>\n</li>\n</ul><p>And the basics:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>UNIX environments, bash and git<br>\n</li>\n<li>Knowledgeable about web protocols, application servers and web servers<br>\n</li>\n<li>Comfortable with HTML, CSS and JavaScript<br>\n</li>\n</ul><p>Bonus points  </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Comfortable with TDD and pair programming/pair designing<br>\n</li>\n<li>Ideally, full software-lifecycle development experience, from inception to releasing updates to systems in production<br>\n</li>\n<li>Modern web client development frameworks, eg: React, AngularJS<br>\n</li>\n<li>DevOps experience<br>\n</li>\n<li>Mentoring<br>\n</li>\n</ul><p>A great saga needs all sorts of heroes  </p>\n\n<p>Making games is fun. Especially when you do it with people who share the same idea of what makes a good workplace, great. We design games for everyone, no matter where they are or who they are, and we employ all sorts of people from all kinds of backgrounds to bring them to life. Truth is, we simply can\u2019t expect diversity in our players and originality in our games without first nurturing it in our people. A great saga needs all sorts of heroes. And that\u2019s it.</p>\n\n<p>We\u2019re Seriously Playful  </p>\n\n<p>Officially, we\u2019re a leading interactive entertainment company for the mobile world. Unofficially, we\u2019re a serious business that\u2019s not afraid to have fun. Every day at King, we mix intuition with logic, art with science and magic with mathematics to create the games the world loves to play. Together with our parent company Activision Blizzard, our mission is to bring moments of magic to everyday life. If you think this is something you can help us achieve, let\u2019s talk.</p>',
      '<p>Want to join our Kingdom? You\u2019ll find all you need to apply, plus more information on our culture, values and benefits, including relocation packages at <a href=\'http://jobs.king.com\'>http://jobs.king.com</a>. All applications should be made in English.</p>',
