      'Build & Deploy Engineer',
      'MACHESNEY PARK',
      'Full Time',
      '<p>Practice Velocity is seeking a Build &amp; Deploy Engineer to the join our growing team.  This is a newly created position that will be supporting our R&amp;D department. </p>\n\n<p>The Engineer\u2019s primary function is to automate and maintain all aspects of the build and deploy process of Practice Velocity\u2019s software development lifecycle. Responsibilities include, but are not limited to: version control, continuous integration, release engineering, release management facilitation, and continuous delivery of software programs and applications.</p>\n\n<p>So what does PV offer?</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A collaborative and open work space where you can get your geek on and chat about code</li>\n<li>Casual dress code \u2013 so bust out those flip flops</li>\n</ul><p>Apply today and find out more because there are too many things to list!</p>\n\n<p>Challenging work in a fast paced environment:</p>\n\n<p>Build Management:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Manage and coordinate Build and Release Management activities, release branches/streams, and merging</li>\n<li>Implement and manage automated deployment, continuous integration, and delivery capabilities</li>\n<li>Partner with software developers, testers, infrastructure teams, and product managers to ensure releases are delivered with a repeatable and auditable process</li>\n<li>Define, implement, and enforce strong software build, deployment and configuration management processes for development, testing, and production systems</li>\n<li>Make recommendations on specific aspects of build and deployment, and continuously strive towards improvements in process and productivity through technology improvements</li>\n</ul><p>Release Management:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Coordinate and manage multiple, complex application releases across different software platforms and development teams</li>\n<li>Track and coordinate with product owners and release manager on release milestones and related dependencies</li>\n<li>Partner with IT operations team to ensure smooth deployments into the production environment via tooling</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot, debug, and correct issues</li>\n<li>Provide second tier support for developers and IT related to build and deploy automation</li>\n<li>Compliance to internal design, coding, and documentation standards</li>\n</ul><p>***We will not be able to provide sponsorship (i.e. H1B Visa) now or in the future.</p>\n\n<p>Skills you bring:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>At least two years of experience with C# development</li>\n<li>At least two years using continuous integration and continuous deployment</li>\n<li>Experience as a Build and Release Engineer, or similar role</li>\n<li>Experience with continuous integration build systems (e.g. Jenkins, Team City, etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience with Visual Studio development environment</li>\n<li>Experience with MSBuild</li>\n<li>Web application setup and deployment in a Microsoft environment</li>\n<li>Experience with multiple source control systems</li>\n<li>Experience with PowerShell scripting and batch programming</li>\n</ul><p>Preferred:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with github.com is a plus</li>\n<li>Experience with automated provisioning systems (Chef, Puppet, etc.)</li>\n<li>MCSD, MCAD or MCPD certification a plus</li>\n</ul><p>Every team member at Practice Velocity exhibits our core values:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Team players</li>\n<li>Positive energy</li>\n<li>Continuous improvement</li>\n<li>Clients win</li>\n</ul>',
