      '<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Architect / Develop / Configure the software and tools to help the Digital Delivery team great online products and services based on user needs and business objectives</p></li>\n<li><p>Assess user needs, design a solution and deliver working software then take that through development stages, thus contribute to its continuous improvement.</p></li>\n<li><p>Design, develop and maintain, test and document code / configuration for applications and platforms. Code will adhere to internal coding standards.</p></li>\n<li><p>Contribute towards the development of our tools, services and platforms.</p></li>\n<li><p>Participate in the creation of attractive interfaces, focusing on driving customer engagement through intuitive, coherent and elegant user experience</p></li>\n<li><p>Ensure the technical solution is in line with the system architecture</p></li>\n<li><p>Marinate existing code and propose changes and improvements based on best practices. Review development deliverables (during design and code reviews)</p></li>\n</ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>University degree in Information Technology or equivalent</p></li>\n<li><p>Experience in Distributed Microservices Architecture (event based)</p></li>\n<li><p>Development experience with different languages and frameworks in both Server and Client (Java, GraphQL, Rest APIs, Javascript, Typescript, Spring Boot, Angular, Ngrx, React, React Native, Redux)</p></li>\n<li><p>Deployment experience with Docker, Vagrant, Jenkins, Kubernetes, AWS</p></li>\n<li><p>Experience with apps, e-shops, portals and public websites</p></li>\n<li><p>Solid background in performance optimization</p></li>\n<li><p>Good troubleshooting skills</p></li>\n<li><p>Good technical and conceptual skills</p></li>\n<li><p>Fluent in English, German would be a big plus</p></li>\n</ul><p>Please note, that to be considered for this position, you must either be a Swiss resident or a EU passport holder. We cannot process any work visa for non-EU citizens.</p>\n\n<p>At Sunrise, you will be working in a dynamic environment where a lot can be achieved through dedication. A wide range of opportunities for professional development will be available to you. In addition to progressive employee benefits, you will receive attractive telecommunications offers.</p>\n\n<p>We believe that teamwork is the key to making work fun. Do you agree? Then seize the moment and apply online!</p>',
