      'Full Time',
      '<p><b>Are you the software engineer who can improve our applications and introduce new technologies?</b></p>\n\n<p><b>Software Engineer (Java) Transaction Channels<br>\nUtrecht, 36/40 hours per week</b></p>\n\n<p><b>Your position</b><br>\nAs a Software Engineer Java you will be an active member of our DevOps team. You\u2019ll be working together with other software engineers, test analysts, ops engineers and business analysts. They will teach you the tricks of the trade, and coach you. You will have ample opportunity to grow and become an even more valuable T shaped professional.</p>\n\n<p>You will collaborate with other disciplines/roles. Together you are responsible for the development/operations life cycle of in-house applications. Our applications are produced to development/test standards, corporate architecture policies including security and data privacy guidelines.</p>\n\n<p>As a software engineer you will be responsible for maintaining and improving your application(s) and for running these applications within IT Systems. Besides the change activities, you also integrally support the applications based on your knowledge. Testing analysis and automated testing are an part of your job.</p>\n\n<p>Working in a DevOps team means you are capable of taking over the basic activities of other DevOps team members when necessary. These activities include; support, analysis, development and testing.</p>\n\n<p><b>Our department</b><br>\nTransaction Channels offers payment functionalities to our customers via several channels; via internet banking, via API or by direct host to host solutions. We deliver functionality for both retail and wholesale customers. We allow customers to make payments, download and search in their transactions, use iDeal and assign to employees and many more transactions services needed by customers.\nOur motto is: \u2018our clients keep moving, so we keep improving\u2019. We focus on providing the best possible experience for Rabobank\u2019s customers by working in a doing-improving cycle. We believe in transparency and adapting the plan to changing circumstances in order to grow. We emphasize personal ownership of products, services and your own development. As a department we co-own all products and portlets and decide together on the direction to go in. We need the most up to date skills &amp; tools in order to perform and maybe even most important: We want to have a lot of fun working at Transaction Channels! </p>\n\n<p>Transaction Channels is part of the Payment Solutions domain within the IT Systems organization. The domain Payment Solutions ensures the continuity and renewal of IT for the chains within Payment Solutions. A 9+ customer experience and current developments such as mobile payments, international banking, instant payments, and new European legislation ask for flexible, reliable and excellent solutions. Government and supervisors pay great attention to the stability and security of our IT systems.</p>\n\n<p><b>Your profile</b><br></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A bachelor\u2019s or master\u2019s degree in information technology or engineering<br>\n</li>\n<li>Several years of experience as a software engineer, in a Java development environment, using current frameworks, tools and techniques<br>\n</li>\n<li>Experience in working in Devops teams, using extensive automation, Continuous Integration / Continuous Deployment and working towards Continuous Delivery<br>\n</li>\n<li>A passion for improvement and introducing new technologies, processes and practices<br>\n</li>\n<li>Experience of programming for the cloud is a prerequisite<br>\n</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Analysis, Monitoring and continuity of applications<br>\n</li>\n<li>Knowledge of ITIL processes (IPCC) and compliancy requirements<br>\n</li>\n<li>Good commandment of the Dutch and English language, in writing and speech<br>\n</li>\n</ul><p><b>Your competencies</b><br>\nBesides the Rabobank core competencies of <b>Customer focus and Collaboration</b>, the following competencies are required for this position:<br></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Result driven<br>\n</li>\n<li>Inspire and influence<br>\n</li>\n<li>Organize and monitor<br>\n</li>\n<li>Initiate improvements<br>\n</li>\n<li>Communication and social skills<br>\n</li>\n</ul><p><b>What we offer</b><br>\nRabobank offers a competitive salary and fringe benefits. Your salary depends on your education, knowledge and experience.</p>\n\n<p><i>An indication of your salary is 45k to 65k a year (at 40 hours a week), with an excellent pension, fringe benefits and training opportunities.</i></p>\n\n<p><b>Additional information</b><br>\nIf you have any questions about the application procedure, please contact Ronald Gill, recruiter, +31 6 2043 9615.</p>\n\n<p><b>How to apply</b><br>\nIf you are interested in this position, please send your letter of application, including job number and detailed CV in English, to Ronald Gill, recruiter, using <a href=\'https://rabobank.heeft-vacatures.nl/software_engineer_java_utrecht/217443/V819/solliciteren\'>this link</a>.</p>\n\n<p><i>The application procedure can include an assessment.</i></p>\n\n<p><i>The Rabobank Group screens all interns and new employees according to the \u2018Rabobank Screening Regulation\u2019 in order to ascertain whether the applicant may hold a position at Rabobank.</i></p>\n\n<p><i>Offers from agencies are not appreciated.</i></p>',
      '<p><a href=\'https://rabobank.heeft-vacatures.nl/software_engineer_java_utrecht/217443/V819/solliciteren\'>klik hier om te solliciteren!</a>.</p>',
