      '<p>As a seasoned executive with experience in a global leadership role, you will report to the Chief Operating Officer, and will also serve as a vital member of the global executive team.\nWe are an organization where acquisitions of software companies are one of our primary goals. You will play a significant role in the acquisition of some of these organizations and will be expected to lead the transformation of any acquired company within a short time frame. Our plan for 2018 is the acquisition of 50 companies.\nYou will be expected to run a world-class 2,500+ person Software Engineering organization using revolutionary and radically differentiated processes. In parallel, you will run operations across a variety of disciplines including Software Engineering, SaaSOps, IT Ops, Support and Finance. \u00a0You will be expected to hire, coach and manage 5-15 SVPs of Software Engineering managing global groups in our factory-like processes with quantifiable business results.\nYou will be expected to be an expert at aggressive goal setting and derive weekly productivity improvements to drive significant levels of value and productivity at much higher levels than in most companies. You must continuously improve the quality of your teams using our global talent sourcing. You will leverage your technical depth as a former developer and architect to set a personal standard for excellence.\nYou are expected to be proficient at doing deep-dives into problem-solving with your teams and able to leverage past technical expertise in Software Development, Quality Assurance, Cloud Infrastructure, and automated deployments using CI/CD tools.\nYou should be capable of working closely with our F500 customer executives as well as key executives within ESW Capital. \u00a0The expectation is that you are a seasoned professional with excellent English communication skills that can effectively manage executive relationships.</p>\n\n<p>KEY RESPONSIBILITIES<br>\nBe a key contributor in our acquisition process and transform acquired companies within 3 months\nAttain continuous process improvements across multiple operations disciplines including Software Engineering, SaaSOps, IT Ops, Support and Finance.\nHire, coach and manage 5-15 SVP-level executives owning a wide variety of critical business functions, but primarily focus on Software Engineering.</p>\n\n<p>CANDIDATE REQUIREMENTS<br>\nBachelor\u2019s Degree in Computer Science is mandatory (MS or PhD preferred).\n20+ years engineering experience in a leadership role managing multiple teams across multiple products and technologies. This is a global leadership role for a seasoned executive, not a first executive role for a great software development manager.\nProven track record running a 1,250+ person Software Engineering and Operations organization.\nBe proficient at doing deep-dives into problem-solving with your teams and able to leverage past technical expertise in Software Development, Quality Assurance, Cloud Infrastructure, and automated deployments using CI/CD tools. \nSpent at least 5 years in a hands-on software coding and architecture role.\nSpent at least 10 years leading engineering managers Managed an annual IT budget in excess of $100m Recent experience with DevOps and Cloud architecture. We live in the Cloud.\nExperience with high-end enterprise systems deployed in environments of F500 corporation complexity.</p>',
